<!doctype qwertz system>

<manpage title="SIGNALJOB" sectnum="3" date='"20 November 2001"'
    footer='"CPLANT MANPAGE"' main='"Cplant Runtime Libraries"'>


<sect1> NAME
    <p>
CplantSignalJob
    </p>


<sect1> SYNOPSIS
    <p>
    <bf/#include &lt;cplant.h>/
    </p>
    <p>
    <bf/int CplantSignalJob(int /<it/sig/<bf/, jobFamilyInfo */<it/otherjob/<bf/)/
    </p>

<sect1> DESCRIPTION
    <p>
    The function <bf/CplantSignalJob/ causes the specified signal
    to be sent to all processes in the specified application.  
    <it/otherjob/
    is a handle returned by <bf/CplantSpawnJob/, <bf/CplantMyParent/
    or <bf/CplantMySelf/. 
    </p> 

<sect1> RETURN VALUE
    <p>
    This function return -1 on error, and 0 on success.  
    </p>

<sect1> SEE ALSO
    <p>
    <bf/CplantSpawnJob/
    <bf/CplantMyParent/
    <bf/CplantMySelf/
    </p>

</manpage>
